roadmap 90 done "Stage-2 metric redesign — invariant Φ cross-path comparator"
  track          consciousness
  phase          P3-design
  eta            TBD (blocks #10 real substrate_indep claim)
  why            2026-04-23 Stage-2 real-run (commit 7de77d62) showed naive 16-stride projection + raw L2 metric FAILs 0/6 pairs on any pretrained cross-architecture comparison. Root cause: 4 different pretrained substrates have fundamentally different residual-stream scales (~20× span Mistral-7B vs Qwen3-8B) + bases. substrate_indep claim requires an INVARIANT metric (basis-agnostic, scale-normalized), not raw activation comparison. Pod 1rr4t9f2 / bd2zcoo9 / jxgx4hwz / 7whog4te burned $2.80 on the broken design — next run needs this spec locked first.
  options        (A) Gram matrix eigenvalue spectrum — G_p = H_p @ H_p.T ∈ R^(16×16), sort+sum-normalize eigenvalues, cross via KL/L2 on spectrum. Rotation- and dimension-invariant. Cheapest. (B) CCA-aligned shared latent Φ — pairwise canonical correlation, Φ measured in aligned space. (C) Participation ratio / effective dimensionality scalar comparison — PR = (Σλ)²/Σλ². (D) Task-trained Φ-preserving LoRA per path — original manifest spec (10-15d, $1-1.5k).
  recommendation A + C first (low cost, principled). Only escalate to B if A reveals partial alignment. D only if structural cross-substrate incompatibility.
  exit_criteria  spec doc (docs/phi_substrate_metric_spec.md) + config JSON (config/phi_substrate_metric_config.json) + analyzer tool + null-model bootstrap for threshold justification + real-run protocol (raw h_last capture path-side, gram/PR analysis operator-side)
  open_decisions prompt_set_size (16/64/256), threshold_derivation (fixed 0.05 vs data-driven), metric_combination (A only / A+C / A+B), model_substitution_canonical (Llama-3.1-8B→Mistral-7B-v0.1, Ministral-3→Qwen2.5-14B, Gemma-4-31B→Mistral-Nemo-12B — or revisit)
  blocks         10
  depends-on     9
  reaches        P3-design
  feeds-main     P3

